Conway's Game of Life implementation complete. All 9 tests passing via the TDD Red-Green-Refactor cycle with specialized agents:

1. Empty input returns empty array
2. Single live cell dies (underpopulation)
3. Two adjacent live cells die (underpopulation)
4. Block still life unchanged
5. Vertical blinker oscillates to horizontal
6. Survival with 3 neighbors
7. Overpopulation with >3 neighbors
8. Reproduction with exactly 3 neighbors
9. Negative coordinates handled

Implementation uses sparse representation with candidate cells (live cells + their neighbors), applying Conway's rules via a single filter expression.
